comments.body:
{quote}
One thing I'm not quite sure is that if we still need SHUFFLE_SORT. Ideally it should only be used for total order, but we can also achieve that with MR shuffle and setting #reducer to 1. I think hive forces #reducer to 1 for order by query, right?
{quote}
Yes, MR does total ordering by setting reducer to 1. Yes, in Spark, we can achieve the same thing with MR styled shuffer + 1 reducer. Historically, Spark didn't do a good job on Shuffle_SORT, but I heard they have made improvement lately. On the other hand, having 1 reducer isn't good either.

I think for now we keep both, but later we can do some benchmarking to see which performs better.
